  "prompt": "Why does my vagina smell fishy after intercourse and a man has ejaculated inside me?",
  "response": "A fishy odor following intercourse can be caused by several factors, including:\n\n1. **Bacterial Vaginosis (BV)**: This is the most common cause of a fishy smell. It occurs due to an imbalance of bacteria in the vagina, and sexual activity can sometimes trigger it.\n\n2. **Sexually Transmitted Infections (STIs)**: Certain STIs, such as trichomoniasis, can lead to unusual odors. \n\n3. **Semen Interaction**: The ejaculate can cause a temporary change in the vaginal environment, potentially leading to an odor.\n\n4. **Poor Hygiene**: Insufficient cleaning after sex can also lead to odors.\n\n5. **Diet and Lifestyle**: Certain foods and lifestyle choices can affect body odors, including vaginal odors.\n\nIf you notice persistent or severe odors, changes in color or consistency of discharge, or other symptoms (like itching or irritation), it's important to consult a healthcare professional for an accurate diagnosis and appropriate treatment.",
